'''Polyvinyl nitrate''' ('''PVN''') is a [[polymer]]ic  [[explosive material]], an [[ester]] of [[nitric acid]] and [[polyvinyl alcohol]]. It is prepared by [[nitration]] of polyvinyl alcohol or [[transesterification]] of [[polyvinyl acetate]]. It is a [[thermoplastic]] substance with softening zone between 30-45 °C, depending on the molecular weight of the starting polyvinyl alcohol.

Polyvinyl nitrate can be used in some moldable [[propellant]]s and [[explosive]]s.

