{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
A '''relative bearing indicator''' ('''RBI''') shows the [[bearing (navigation)|bearing]] of some source relative to a vehicle carrying a detector. It is most commonly used in conjunction with an ADF (automatic direction finder) in an aircraft navigating with the aid of an [[Non-directional beacon|NDB (non-directional beacon)]].

